{"questionId":"26875","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A Principal would like to compare the students in his school with a national standard.&nbsp;He decides to give a test to eight students made up of four boys and four girls. One of&nbsp;the teachers offers to find the volunteers from his class.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The marks out of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn></math>, for the students who took the test, are:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>29</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>38</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>37</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>18</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>27</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>31</mn><mo>.</mo></math></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For the eight students find</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>the standard deviation of the marks.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>29815</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>≈</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>30</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26875","referenceCode":"22M.2.AHL.TZ1.3b.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"the standard deviation of the marks.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.3—Mean, median, mode. Mean of grouped data, standard deviation. Quartiles, IQR"],"memberSec